[normal]Written evidence from the Police and Crime Commissioner for Leicestershire [CST0076][bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The following questions have been asked by Public Administration Select Committee.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]What, if any, targets do you set for your police force?
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]What impact do you think this has on police recording crime practices?
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]How do you assure yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct?
[normal]•
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Taking each in turn:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]What, if any, targets do you set for your police force?[bold]The 
[normal]Police and Crime Plan 2013-2017 Executive Summary
[normal] lists the targets that have been set for the 2013/14 Financial Year.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]What impact do you think this has on police recording crime practices?[bold]The setting of targets has no impact on police recording crime practices in Leicestershire, HMIC have reaffirmed this in their most recent inspections of Crime Recording Standards in the Force area.
